1
00:00:02,798 --> 00:00:03,798
Victor?

2
00:00:05,384 --> 00:00:07,673
Victor, I need your help
with something.

3
00:00:07,966 --> 00:00:09,773
Honey, I got water boiling.

4
00:00:10,747 --> 00:00:12,311
Dinner can wait.

5
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:26,651
Want to help me out of this?

6
00:00:43,983 --> 00:00:46,859
You get it hard
on an old man, don't you?

7
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:48,531
I do, don't I?

8
00:01:05,837 --> 00:01:07,771
How did I get so lucky?

9
00:01:08,319 --> 00:01:09,235
You didn't.

10
00:01:10,108 --> 00:01:11,861
I'm using you for sex.

11
00:01:12,110 --> 00:01:13,788
I love you, Clara.

12
00:01:13,913 --> 00:01:15,442
I love you more.

13
00:01:17,635 --> 00:01:19,161
I'll be back in an hour.

14
00:01:19,329 --> 00:01:21,080
Where are you off to?

15
00:01:22,198 --> 00:01:23,540
Strawberries.

16
00:01:24,728 --> 00:01:25,874
Champagne.

17
00:01:28,510 --> 00:01:30,177
Don't you leave this bed.

18
00:01:51,117 --> 00:01:52,407
My God, Leo.

19
00:01:55,282 --> 00:01:56,615
What am I going to do?

20
00:02:04,533 --> 00:02:06,041
Did you kill your husband?!

21
00:02:06,209 --> 00:02:07,562
No. I loved my husband.

22
00:02:07,687 --> 00:02:09,685
If you're acquitted,
you'll be a billionaire.

23
00:02:09,810 --> 00:02:11,985
- How does that make me feel?
- My client has no comment.

24
00:02:12,110 --> 00:02:13,674
What's it like sleeping alone now?

25
00:02:13,842 --> 00:02:15,259
By the way, how was the sex?

26
00:02:15,708 --> 00:02:16,975
Get her inside.

27
00:02:19,212 --> 00:02:20,473
What station are you from?

28
00:02:20,641 --> 00:02:21,641
Your credentials?

29
00:02:21,766 --> 00:02:24,143
A public street in a free country.
I don't need credentials.

30
00:02:25,359 --> 00:02:26,543
You're no journalist.

31
00:02:26,668 --> 00:02:28,522
Someone told you
to ask those questions.

32
00:02:29,226 --> 00:02:30,357
I'm doing my job.

33
00:02:30,839 --> 00:02:32,588
I think I can guess who for.

34
00:02:35,334 --> 00:02:37,427
What are you getting off Mrs. Musso?

35
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:39,450
More sadness than guilt really.

36
00:02:40,987 --> 00:02:42,866
The evidence is rock solid.

37
00:02:43,145 --> 00:02:45,284
There's a partial print
on a syringe containing cyanide.

38
00:02:45,409 --> 00:02:47,110
No sign of forced entry
in her apartment.

39
00:02:47,235 --> 00:02:49,084
She is the primary beneficiary
of the will.

40
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:51,629
You got all that going for you, Crosby.
What do you need me for?

41
00:02:51,797 --> 00:02:54,497
Never underestimate
the value of an expert witness.

42
00:02:54,622 --> 00:02:56,717
Doc, you wanna do this?

43
00:03:01,479 --> 00:03:02,714
How was the sex?

44
00:03:02,839 --> 00:03:04,068
<i>Hello, Zoe.</i>

45
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:05,895
It's been a long time.

46
00:03:06,146 --> 00:03:07,686
What do you need?
A reference?

47
00:03:08,869 --> 00:03:10,773
I haven't had any trouble
getting offers so far.

48
00:03:11,353 --> 00:03:13,786
You sent one of your minions
to ask vicious and personal questions

49
00:03:13,911 --> 00:03:16,487
to my client just so you could read
her reactions on TV.

50
00:03:16,655 --> 00:03:18,489
I can't hear you.
No, can you say that again.

51
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:20,533
Hear me now?

52
00:03:22,401 --> 00:03:24,300
- Clear as a bell.
- Counselor.

53
00:03:25,831 --> 00:03:28,005
I'd like to speak
with my ex-husband in private,

54
00:03:28,130 --> 00:03:29,208
if that's all right.

55
00:03:34,193 --> 00:03:35,059
Absolutely.

56
00:03:35,184 --> 00:03:37,685
I'd like an answer by the end
of the business day, if you don't mind.

57
00:03:37,810 --> 00:03:40,511
Otherwise, I gotta go to Rayder firm,
I don't really want to do that.

58
00:03:42,473 --> 00:03:43,650
Fair enough.

59
00:03:49,971 --> 00:03:51,096
Let me guess.

60
00:03:51,394 --> 00:03:53,384
He wants you to be
his expert witness?

61
00:03:54,276 --> 00:03:56,376
Your client is hiding something.

62
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:58,313
Probably of a sexual nature,

63
00:03:58,438 --> 00:04:00,914
granted that is wishful
thinking on my part.

64
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:04,285
She's bringing that hand up to her face.
She's got a secret.

65
00:04:04,670 --> 00:04:07,538
I will tear you apart on the stand, Cal.
And you know it.

66
00:04:07,706 --> 00:04:09,097
Nice charm, that is.

67
00:04:09,510 --> 00:04:11,125
You think
she didn't kill her husband?

68
00:04:11,772 --> 00:04:13,562
- Yes, I do.
- What makes you so sure?

69
00:04:13,687 --> 00:04:16,491
All the evidence is circumstantial.
And as for motive, there is none.

70
00:04:16,616 --> 00:04:18,807
My client didn't want for anything.

71
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:21,621
It was a loving
and faithful marriage.

72
00:04:22,635 --> 00:04:23,470
An alibi?

73
00:04:26,577 --> 00:04:28,767
- How much is she paying you?
- Exactly what I'm worth.

74
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:30,494
Drinks are on you then.

75
00:04:31,204 --> 00:04:33,814
Still... no alibi.

76
00:04:34,566 --> 00:04:36,513
The trauma of finding
her husband dead

77
00:04:36,638 --> 00:04:39,487
caused Clara to lose her memory
for the 40 minutes

78
00:04:39,612 --> 00:04:42,573
between the last time she saw him alive
and when she discovered his body.

79
00:04:48,057 --> 00:04:50,045
Look at it. I mean, really.

80
00:04:50,562 --> 00:04:53,115
She is pushing
those tears out, she is.

81
00:04:53,585 --> 00:04:54,543
She's faking it.

82
00:04:59,970 --> 00:05:02,343
We both know
that this "science" of yours

83
00:05:02,511 --> 00:05:04,220
has a serious margin for error.

84
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:05,933
It won't cut it in a court of law.

85
00:05:06,058 --> 00:05:06,931
What will?

86
00:05:07,331 --> 00:05:10,976
Tears for a dead husband
that left her $1.2 billion?

87
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:13,871
I know why you're doing this.
You're not going to get under my skin.

88
00:05:13,996 --> 00:05:14,996
Or my skirt.

89
00:05:15,357 --> 00:05:18,108
That's a lie, that is.
I mean the skin part.

90
00:05:18,276 --> 00:05:20,744
Is this funny to you?
The most important case of my career?

91
00:05:20,869 --> 00:05:23,545
I haven't even taken
the bloody job yet, Zoe.

92
00:05:23,670 --> 00:05:26,239
Unlike you, I don't need to have studied
amazonian pigmies for 6 years

93
00:05:26,364 --> 00:05:28,452
- to know that that's a lie.
- You want me to do this.

94
00:05:28,914 --> 00:05:30,996
You don't know why you do.
But you do.

95
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:33,458
Did I say
"serious margin for error"?

96
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:35,643
I was being generous.

97
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:37,544
Or couldn't you tell.

98
00:05:38,744 --> 00:05:40,229
It's going to be a shame

99
00:05:40,354 --> 00:05:42,238
to disappoint you in the courtroom.

100
00:05:43,426 --> 00:05:46,261
La <i><font color="#ff0000">Lie</font> <font color="#ffffff">to</font><font color="#ff0000"> team</font></i> présente :

101
00:06:11,746 --> 00:06:13,288
Épisode 213 : <i>The Whole Truth</i>

102
00:06:13,987 --> 00:06:16,333
<i>How can anyone think Clara
killed her husband?</i>

103
00:06:16,501 --> 00:06:17,918
<i>I've been friends for 10 years.</i>

104
00:06:18,086 --> 00:06:19,936
<i>There's no way
she could have done this.</i>

105
00:06:20,583 --> 00:06:23,465
Gotta love how everyone comes out
of the woodwork on cases like this.

106
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:25,503
They've gotta get
their 15 minutes somehow.

107
00:06:25,628 --> 00:06:27,552
By turning this woman's life
into a circus.

108
00:06:27,677 --> 00:06:29,820
Yeah. We're all part
of that circus now.

109
00:06:29,945 --> 00:06:30,995
Prosecution.

110
00:06:31,349 --> 00:06:34,018
Foster, you're prepping witnesses.
You two, you get jury watch.

111
00:06:34,186 --> 00:06:35,978
Read the jurors for the whole trial?

112
00:06:36,146 --> 00:06:38,981
Track 'em individually, see what makes
them tick. But look at them as a group.

113
00:06:39,289 --> 00:06:41,984
I wanna know which way they're leaning.
The leaders, the followers.

114
00:06:42,749 --> 00:06:43,569
Well go on.

115
00:06:49,079 --> 00:06:51,076
You're not just doing this
to push Zoe's buttons.

116
00:06:51,579 --> 00:06:53,037
There's something else going on.

117
00:06:53,382 --> 00:06:54,997
This is about justice, Foster.

118
00:06:55,165 --> 00:06:57,041
There's something else.
Zoe-related.

119
00:06:58,715 --> 00:07:00,169
Justice for a murder victim.

120
00:07:00,487 --> 00:07:02,588
By avoiding my question,
you just answered it.

121
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,716
I just hope for all our sakes,
you know what you're doing.

122
00:07:06,270 --> 00:07:07,529
Join the club.

123
00:07:09,448 --> 00:07:11,353
Six of the jurors
look convinced Clara is guilty

124
00:07:11,478 --> 00:07:12,916
just from the opening arguments.

125
00:07:13,041 --> 00:07:15,601
You could see approval on their faces
every time the prosecutor talked.

126
00:07:16,028 --> 00:07:18,604
Maybe. But these two
are for the defense.

127
00:07:19,284 --> 00:07:21,278
And they've already emerged
as leaders.

128
00:07:21,403 --> 00:07:23,984
Jurors 6, 7 and 11 were looking at them,
gaging their reaction.

129
00:07:24,717 --> 00:07:26,356
Which way you two leaning?

130
00:07:26,930 --> 00:07:29,027
Maybe he wasn't dying
fast enough for her.

131
00:07:29,319 --> 00:07:31,116
The guy was 30 years older
than she is.

132
00:07:31,335 --> 00:07:33,014
So?
So...

133
00:07:33,555 --> 00:07:34,987
It can affect the power dynamic.

134
00:07:35,112 --> 00:07:38,332
Imbalance of power in a relationship
can lead to victimization.

135
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:39,924
That struck a nerve.

136
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,252
That's interesting.

137
00:07:42,941 --> 00:07:44,815
Studies show that the most
successful marriages

138
00:07:44,940 --> 00:07:47,591
are the ones where husbands are at least
5 years older than their wives.

139
00:07:48,146 --> 00:07:51,303
So, being with an older man
broadens your horizons, does it?

140
00:07:53,540 --> 00:07:55,607
I'm sure Clara learned a lot
from Victor.

141
00:07:56,101 --> 00:07:57,768
I'm sure she did,
about denture cream.

142
00:07:58,530 --> 00:07:59,937
You're not listening, again.

143
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:03,524
What Torres is saying is that
she needs to be stimulated, challenged.

144
00:08:05,151 --> 00:08:06,151
By experience.

145
00:08:08,199 --> 00:08:09,863
So, who was this old fart then?

146
00:08:11,524 --> 00:08:12,782
I was talking about Clara.

147
00:08:13,285 --> 00:08:14,359
You weren't.

148
00:08:15,087 --> 00:08:17,996
You connected with a memory,
which I proceeded to belittle.

149
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:21,904
Sorry about that.

150
00:08:26,908 --> 00:08:29,134
You cannot sing
the praises of older men

151
00:08:29,259 --> 00:08:30,926
and then not give up details.

152
00:08:31,799 --> 00:08:32,835
Watch me.

153
00:08:40,437 --> 00:08:41,395
All right.

154
00:08:41,563 --> 00:08:44,025
- You couldn't take me one-on-one?
- Been there, done that.

155
00:08:45,483 --> 00:08:47,064
I promise to play nice today.

156
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:50,110
Last time you said that
you left claw marks.

157
00:08:51,446 --> 00:08:54,050
Do you swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth, nothing but the truth,

158
00:08:54,175 --> 00:08:55,159
so help you God?

159
00:08:55,327 --> 00:08:56,910
- That's not possible.
- Excuse me.

160
00:08:57,696 --> 00:09:00,348
No one can tell the whole truth,
your honor.

161
00:09:00,473 --> 00:09:03,041
It's subjective. It's filtered
through our own experiences.

162
00:09:04,044 --> 00:09:07,448
- That's the real truth.
- How about promising to be honest

163
00:09:07,674 --> 00:09:09,298
to the best of your ability?

164
00:09:09,843 --> 00:09:11,815
- Now, you're talking.
- Please, be seated.

165
00:09:11,940 --> 00:09:14,910
- Thank you, your honor.
- Dr., your resume speaks for itself.

166
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:17,472
You're Oxford educated.
You're a doctorate in psychology.

167
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:19,541
And you're a consultant for the FBI.

168
00:09:19,666 --> 00:09:22,561
As you well know,
the key question in this trial is:

169
00:09:22,729 --> 00:09:25,147
"Where was Clara Musso
the night her husband was murdered?"

170
00:09:25,625 --> 00:09:28,186
The defense wants us to believe

171
00:09:28,425 --> 00:09:31,426
that the trauma of finding
her husband dead

172
00:09:32,028 --> 00:09:34,364
has left Mrs. Musso unable to recall

173
00:09:34,532 --> 00:09:36,677
the 40 minutes between leaving him

174
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:38,960
and discovering his corpse.

175
00:09:39,326 --> 00:09:41,095
Dr. Lightman,
in your expert opinion,

176
00:09:41,220 --> 00:09:44,082
does this claim of memory loss
pass the sniff test?

177
00:09:47,744 --> 00:09:48,942
Could you elaborate?

178
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:51,965
It's been proven that some trauma...

179
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,241
warfare...

180
00:09:53,802 --> 00:09:55,093
child abuse...

181
00:09:55,218 --> 00:09:56,678
can cause memory loss.

182
00:09:57,413 --> 00:09:59,514
- An experience with such cases?
- Yeah. Plenty.

183
00:09:59,682 --> 00:10:02,059
I've worked with soldiers,
rape victims.

184
00:10:02,981 --> 00:10:06,188
Memory loss is caused by degradation

185
00:10:06,658 --> 00:10:07,564
or abuse.

186
00:10:07,732 --> 00:10:10,359
Shock of a dead spouse,
that'd be a first.

187
00:10:11,376 --> 00:10:13,070
How about a shock
of committing murder?

188
00:10:13,238 --> 00:10:16,740
Killers have been known
to experience amnesia.

189
00:10:17,337 --> 00:10:18,992
Forensic psychologists
Call it red out.

190
00:10:21,038 --> 00:10:23,163
How common is it to lie,
claiming memory loss?

191
00:10:23,331 --> 00:10:25,582
9 out of 10 people
claiming memory loss are lying.

192
00:10:25,965 --> 00:10:27,042
Why do they do that?

193
00:10:27,210 --> 00:10:30,337
It's easier to say:
"I can't remember".

194
00:10:30,929 --> 00:10:32,663
Than tell the truth.

195
00:10:34,066 --> 00:10:35,434
I have nothing further.

196
00:10:36,656 --> 00:10:37,844
Your witness, counselor.

197
00:10:40,526 --> 00:10:42,808
Permission to treat Dr. Lightman
as a hostile witness?

198
00:10:43,126 --> 00:10:44,518
- Granted.
- Dr. Lightman!

199
00:10:44,780 --> 00:10:46,668
I'm sorry.
Won't happen again, your honor.

200
00:10:46,793 --> 00:10:47,646
Thank you.

201
00:10:49,057 --> 00:10:52,067
Dr. Lightman was born hostile.
He also happens to be my ex-husband.

202
00:10:52,235 --> 00:10:53,652
Guilty as charged.

203
00:10:54,683 --> 00:10:56,777
But, you know, it was my loss.

204
00:10:57,133 --> 00:10:59,616
Because truly she is an angel.

205
00:11:01,056 --> 00:11:03,880
The prosecution has touted
your credentials.

206
00:11:04,005 --> 00:11:06,848
Are we to understand
that you possess the gift

207
00:11:06,973 --> 00:11:09,290
of being able to distinguish
between truth and lies?

208
00:11:09,415 --> 00:11:12,044
No. No. 20 years of research
is not a gift, is it?

209
00:11:12,169 --> 00:11:15,048
You and I know, it's a
bit of a curse, really.

210
00:11:15,614 --> 00:11:16,814
Indeed it was.

211
00:11:17,586 --> 00:11:20,470
In fact, do you recall
being jeered off the stage

212
00:11:20,638 --> 00:11:23,753
while keynoting the Harvard global
psychology conference in 2005?

213
00:11:23,878 --> 00:11:25,017
Yeah. I do. Yeah!

214
00:11:25,592 --> 00:11:27,242
Yeah, and it's bonkers.

215
00:11:27,767 --> 00:11:31,315
Right? Because I could have
sworn that they were cheering.

216
00:11:32,028 --> 00:11:34,860
They called it pop psychology.
Voodoo science.

217
00:11:35,028 --> 00:11:37,112
I think it's because
they're scared of me.

218
00:11:38,615 --> 00:11:42,534
4 years ago when we were still married,
you accused my boss of sleeping with me.

219
00:11:42,702 --> 00:11:44,745
- The gloves are off now!
- Objection your honor!

220
00:11:44,913 --> 00:11:48,623
- That's immaterial.
- Dr. Lightman, last warning. Overruled.

221
00:11:49,351 --> 00:11:51,522
Didn't it come out eventually
that my boss...

222
00:11:51,647 --> 00:11:54,171
A man... was in fact... gay?

223
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:56,998
Yeah. Yeah, it did. Yeah.

224
00:11:57,572 --> 00:12:00,010
I was way off the mark on that one.

225
00:12:00,330 --> 00:12:02,130
But I mean, I was jealous.

226
00:12:02,585 --> 00:12:05,152
I was young,
I was head over heels in love.

227
00:12:05,277 --> 00:12:09,144
By day I'm a scientist.
But by night, I'm fallible.

228
00:12:09,668 --> 00:12:10,729
I'm only human.

229
00:12:11,724 --> 00:12:14,566
I'm not questioning your humanity.
And certainly not your fallibility.

230
00:12:14,734 --> 00:12:17,283
- That's a relief.
- You are here because of your expertise

231
00:12:17,408 --> 00:12:19,780
in psychology and lying.
I'm challenging that.

232
00:12:20,335 --> 00:12:22,644
Your flagrant manipulation
of the jury notwithstanding.

233
00:12:22,769 --> 00:12:24,519
OK. But when you say that

234
00:12:24,961 --> 00:12:27,079
your client is innocent,
you don't believe that.

235
00:12:27,488 --> 00:12:30,381
Again, you misjudge my thoughts
because I know my client is innocent.

236
00:12:30,506 --> 00:12:32,378
Why don't you want to hear
the science then?

237
00:12:32,503 --> 00:12:36,206
Your testimony is limited
to scientific context

238
00:12:36,331 --> 00:12:38,401
not specific opinions
on who's lying.

239
00:12:38,526 --> 00:12:40,926
You want to hear the whole truth?
That woman over there,

240
00:12:41,094 --> 00:12:43,345
- Your client, the black widow...
- Control yourself!

241
00:12:43,513 --> 00:12:44,986
When she says she doesn't know...

242
00:12:45,111 --> 00:12:46,848
Dr. Lightman.
Control yourself.

243
00:12:47,016 --> 00:12:48,558
She's lying, and that's a fact.

244
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:51,228
Control yourself or I will have
the judge control you!

245
00:12:51,396 --> 00:12:53,063
Her? Do me a favor, look at her.

246
00:12:53,231 --> 00:12:55,097
She's having a tough time
controlling herself.

247
00:12:55,222 --> 00:12:59,086
Marshall, please remove this witness
before I hold him in contempt.

248
00:12:59,211 --> 00:13:02,406
look at her. Bulging eyes,
