And you gave him that injection,
didn't you?

736
00:39:00,839 --> 00:39:02,381
- Your honor!
- Take your seat.

737
00:39:04,692 --> 00:39:06,321
Victor was devout.

738
00:39:06,651 --> 00:39:08,022
I mean, to him

739
00:39:08,303 --> 00:39:10,354
suicide was a mortal sin.

740
00:39:13,342 --> 00:39:14,977
I couldn't say no to my friend.

741
00:39:15,686 --> 00:39:18,058
Which is why you never told him
that Clara was stealing.

742
00:39:18,961 --> 00:39:20,156
Because he was dying.

743
00:39:20,281 --> 00:39:22,567
Why break his heart on top
of everything else?

744
00:39:23,837 --> 00:39:25,946
Do you have proof
it wasn't a murder?

745
00:39:31,406 --> 00:39:34,454
- He left a video explaining.
- Now that

746
00:39:34,922 --> 00:39:35,922
right there.

747
00:39:36,949 --> 00:39:38,208
That is shame.

748
00:39:40,624 --> 00:39:42,757
I think his widow
has a right to see that.

749
00:39:46,551 --> 00:39:48,312
But I didn't imagine that

750
00:39:48,593 --> 00:39:50,095
I'd meet a woman

751
00:39:50,263 --> 00:39:52,906
who would understand me
so completely.

752
00:39:53,504 --> 00:39:55,449
Our marriage was a gift, Clara.

753
00:39:56,961 --> 00:39:58,988
Happiest 10 years of my life.

754
00:39:59,984 --> 00:40:01,895
I wouldn't let anything
tarnish that.

755
00:40:02,020 --> 00:40:04,490
Zoe says that Leo is

756
00:40:04,712 --> 00:40:06,611
pleading guilty
to obstruction of justice

757
00:40:06,938 --> 00:40:09,681
and manslaughter.
And they're working out a deal.

758
00:40:10,426 --> 00:40:11,865
That's good then.

759
00:40:14,271 --> 00:40:15,698
Thank you for everything.

760
00:40:17,768 --> 00:40:19,757
I should have trusted you sooner.

761
00:40:20,126 --> 00:40:21,558
I could say the same thing.

762
00:40:26,877 --> 00:40:29,275
I've got a meeting waiting.

763
00:40:37,533 --> 00:40:39,674
She's a beautiful woman.

764
00:40:41,662 --> 00:40:42,773
She's my Leo.

765
00:40:45,273 --> 00:40:46,536
What about Zoe?

766
00:40:47,601 --> 00:40:49,706
To say you stopped loving someone
you once loved

767
00:40:49,831 --> 00:40:52,022
more than anything else
in the world, I mean

768
00:40:52,147 --> 00:40:54,560
that would be a lie.
But you move on.

769
00:40:55,472 --> 00:40:56,472
Don't you?

770
00:40:57,531 --> 00:40:58,914
You have to move on.

771
00:41:02,443 --> 00:41:04,408
She's my daughter's mum.

772
00:41:07,582 --> 00:41:09,371
Sometimes sparring partner.

773
00:41:10,447 --> 00:41:12,529
Any other women populating
your life?

774
00:41:14,529 --> 00:41:16,515
None you need to worry about.

775
00:41:21,170 --> 00:41:23,509
I'm taking over Victor's businesses
and charities.

776
00:41:24,725 --> 00:41:26,667
People are going to come after me.

777
00:41:27,029 --> 00:41:29,798
They think I'm weak.
I need someone I can trust.

778
00:41:30,446 --> 00:41:31,973
You got my number.

779
00:41:33,026 --> 00:41:34,371
So, to speak.

780
00:41:40,213 --> 00:41:41,991
My point is, right,

781
00:41:43,406 --> 00:41:46,086
that the reason that we won
was 'cause the whole truth came out.

782
00:41:46,817 --> 00:41:49,882
Which no, cause it doesn't
normally happen in a courtroom.

783
00:41:51,332 --> 00:41:52,887
Why'd you take this case?

784
00:41:53,624 --> 00:41:55,595
I thought it'd be a bit of fun.

785
00:41:56,232 --> 00:41:57,806
That's not it.
Not really.

786
00:41:59,761 --> 00:42:01,749
It's your first time out there.

787
00:42:02,404 --> 00:42:04,053
It's a big national case.

788
00:42:05,211 --> 00:42:06,523
You were protecting me?

789
00:42:07,594 --> 00:42:09,314
That's so sweet.

790
00:42:09,852 --> 00:42:11,736
And paternalistic and patronizing.

791
00:42:12,425 --> 00:42:14,132
Yeah. You got a point there.

792
00:42:14,378 --> 00:42:15,816
No, but look. If you get

793
00:42:16,185 --> 00:42:18,368
a guilty woman off,
you're a punch line.

794
00:42:18,840 --> 00:42:20,991
If you convict an innocent man,
you're a joke.

795
00:42:21,664 --> 00:42:23,373
You've worked far too hard

796
00:42:24,360 --> 00:42:25,611
to get where you are.

797
00:42:26,693 --> 00:42:28,400
You deserve a bit of respect.

798
00:42:29,769 --> 00:42:30,755
Not infamy.

799
00:42:33,640 --> 00:42:35,687
Still waiting for you
to get what you deserve.

800
00:42:36,620 --> 00:42:37,953
Well, I'm 2 steps

801
00:42:38,362 --> 00:42:39,764
ahead of the hangman.

802
00:42:44,780 --> 00:42:46,628
Emily's sleeping at a friend's.

803
00:42:47,213 --> 00:42:48,815
What? The whole night?

804
00:42:49,868 --> 00:42:51,540
- All right.
- I'll get the check.

